<subSubSection pageId="87" pageNumber="88" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="87.[151,1436,924,1128]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,1031,1056]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Notes.</emphasis>
A primitively eusocial ground-nester, commonly found in southfacing banks or horizontal ground near streams and rivers (
<bibRefCitation author="Batra" box="[378,509,1068,1093]" firstAuthor="Batra" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="159 - 186" refId="ref83144" refString="Batra, S. W. T. (1964) Behavior of the social bee, Lasioglossum zephyrum, within the nest (Hymenoptera: Halictidae). Insectes Sociaux, 11, 159 - 186. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / bf 02222935" type="journal article" year="1964">Batra 1964</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Batra" box="[523,583,1068,1093]" firstAuthor="Batra" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="359 - 423" refId="ref83193" refString="Batra, S. W. T. (1966) The life cycle and behavior of the primitively social bee, Lasioglossum zephyrum (Halictidae). University of Kansas Science Bulletin, 46, 359 - 423." type="journal article" year="1966">1966</bibRefCitation>
). A well-studied species of halictid bee; for a list of references see 
<bibRefCitation author="Gibbs" firstAuthor="Gibbs" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" pagination="1 - 6" refId="ref88394" refString="Gibbs, J. (2010 a) Atypical wing venation in Dialictus and Hemihalictus and its implications for subgeneric classification of Lasioglossum. Psyche, 2010, 1 - 6. https: // doi. org / 10.1155 / 2010 / 605390" type="journal article" year="2010">Gibbs (2010)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure &amp; Hurd" box="[280,532,1103,1128]" firstAuthor="Moure" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" refId="ref96774" refString="Moure, J. S. &amp; Hurd, P. D. (1987) An annotated catalog of the halictid bees of the Western Hemisphere (Hymenoptera: Halictidae). Smithsonian Institution Press, Washington, D. C., 405 pp." type="book" year="1987">Moure &amp; Hurd (1987)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
